Good bingsu but not the best

Firstly, me and my friends just wanted to share a bowl of injeolmi after tiring day. To my surprise, we were told to spend $40 minimum per person. In order to hit the minimum spending, we upsized our injeolmi to the large size and added one more dessert. To my even greater surprise, they just added more ice to the injeolmi as if I’m just eating a bowl of ice. I just wanted to end of my day on a right note but this stall just ruined my entire trip. 

Oh, and the tiramisu is hell of a trash
Desserts and Korean hot noodles and fried chicken.  Quality is below par. Congested seating like most HK dessert Cafe.
Nice menu although I quite not enjoy the fries as I don't find it crispy enough. But the desserts are awesome!

result.name: Nun Desserts Cafe

reviews.text: 大陸鄉音女店員態度差劣，食物廚房衛生欠佳，難食
充滿特色的韓式刨冰，在旺角逛累，可以在此吃冰、休息及閒聊。草莓雪奶有滿滿的草莓，拍照－流，可說是女生最愛！
完全不值這個價錢, 飲品非常普通, 店員服務一般, 窩夫一點也不鬆脆, 不會再光顧, 令人非常憤怒!!!!
來這已經第三次了，每次都吃不同的雪奶，真的好好味
